create

public Project create()
               throws javax.ejb.CreateException,
                      javax.ejb.EJBException
Returns a new instance. The properties are set to default values, and may be changed by using the appropriate setter methods. The instance may be a repository or bean implementation depending on how this home's factory was obtained. If the instance is backed by a persistent implementation, it may not actually be persisted until Project.writeInstance() is called on the instance (and the transaction is committed, if the implementation is transaction-aware).
